title: Section 3 Semifinal Pairings Announced
text:
Section 3 Semifinal Pairings Announced Tools 
Story Published: Oct 26, 2015 at 7:22 AM EDT Story Updated: Oct 26, 2015 at 7:22 AM EDT 
A dozen Frontier League teams remain alive in the Section 3 postseason as semifinals get underway this week. Four teams remain alive on the gridiron, along with five in girls' soccer and three in boys' soccer. Dates, times and sites for the semis were released Sunday. On the girls' soccer side, Class B Lowville takes on Westhill at 5:30 p.m. Tuesday at Chittenango High School. The Beaver River girls meets Sauquoit Valley in a Class C semi at 7:30 p.m. the same night and at the same place. On the boys' soccer side Wednesday, Lowville takes on Marcellus in Class B at 5:30 p.m. at Cicero-North Syracuse and IHC takes on Cooperstown in Class C at 5:30 p.m. at Nottingham High School. The other boys' Class C semi Wednesday pits Hamilton against Thousand Islands at 7:30 p.m., also at Nottingham. In girls' Class D soccer Wednesday, Copenhagen battles Poland at 7:30 p.m. at Chittenango. In the other Class D semi, it's Sackets Harbor taking on Cincinnatus at 7:30 p.m. at Camden High School. On the gridiron, Class A Indian River squares off against Whitesboro at 8 p.m. Friday at Chittenango. In Class C, it's General Brown against Utica Notre Dame at 8 p.m. Friday at Fulton High School. In Class D, Sandy Creek goes up against Onondaga at 5 p.m. Friday, also at Fulton. And, in the National Football Foundation semi, Beaver River and Tully meet at 11 a.m. Saturday at Liverpool High School.
